## Conventions

| Convention | Rule |
|---|---|
| Branch name | `<type>/<issue-number>-<kebab-description>` (type ∈ `feature/` `fix/` `chore/` `refactor/`) |
| Branch creation | `gh issue develop <N> --name <branch> --checkout --base main` (canonical issue-to-branch hop; auto-closes issue when PR merges) |
| Spec discipline | Specs ship in the same PR as code. See `docs/methodology.md` §B. |
| Living docs | Update on every ship. See `docs/methodology.md` §G + `<consumer>/CLAUDE.md` §"Documentation Requirements". |

## Context thresholds

| % | Action | Why |
|---|---|---|
| <60% | Work freely. | Cache warm; no concern. |
| ~60% (60–74) | Pay attention; finish current focused work before adding scope. | Quality stays solid here, but it's the right time to wrap a focused unit before piling on more. |
| ~75% (75–84) | Consider `/handoff` (LEAN) or `/compact` at a natural break. | A handoff or compaction here keeps the thread crisp without losing state. |
| ~85%+ | `/handoff` (EMERGENCY) or `/clear`. | The far end of the window; hand off or reset rather than push deeper. |

The % is the fraction of the full context window in use (harness-native `context_window.used_percentage`, the same value the statusline reads).

These bands map to the context-awareness reminder tiers (silent <60 · warn ~60 · suggest-handoff ~75 · urgent ~85) and the `/handoff` doc-detail tiers (FULL <75 · LEAN 75–84 · EMERGENCY ≥85).

Rationale: with a 1M window + native compaction, real pressure is far out, so the bands are intentionally generous — observed agent behavior degrades gradually rather than at a hard cliff (see `docs/methodology.md` §H).

